44
00:04:03,676 --> 00:04:06,440
What?! The brake?!

45
00:04:06,846 --> 00:04:08,581
The emergency brake doesn't work either.

46
00:04:08,581 --> 00:04:10,416
I think somebody did something to it.

47
00:04:10,416 --> 00:04:13,553
We don't have time to discuss that now.
Hurry up and turn around!

48
00:04:13,553 --> 00:04:16,189
I can't! We're in a take.

49
00:04:16,189 --> 00:04:18,858
But there's a cliff ahead, isn't there?

50
00:04:18,858 --> 00:04:20,727
How do you think you're going to
stop the car?

51
00:04:20,727 --> 00:04:21,785
Yuki!

52
00:04:33,072 --> 00:04:35,666
The next one is the last bomb, isn't it?

53
00:04:36,309 --> 00:04:37,537
Mr. Saeba?!

54
00:04:45,151 --> 00:04:47,619
What are you doing? That's where
the bomb is!

55
00:04:55,662 --> 00:04:56,560
Ryo!

56
00:05:18,251 --> 00:05:19,878
The car stopped.

57
00:05:21,354 --> 00:05:23,515
Mr. Saeba, are you all right?

58
00:05:24,157 --> 00:05:28,695
Of course! A comfortable cushion
protected me!

59
00:05:28,695 --> 00:05:30,185
Mr. Saeba!

60
00:05:30,330 --> 00:05:31,331
Miss Yuki!

61
00:05:31,331 --> 00:05:32,798
Miss Yuki!

62
00:05:33,466 --> 00:05:34,734
Ryo!

63
00:05:34,734 --> 00:05:36,964
Are you all right? Did you get hurt?

64
00:05:38,204 --> 00:05:41,207
What went wrong? Did something happen?

65
00:05:41,207 --> 00:05:42,575
Well...

66
00:05:42,575 --> 00:05:44,668
Ah, actually...

67
00:05:45,144 --> 00:05:49,582
The explosion was bigger than I expected,
so I clung to Yuki without thinking,

68
00:05:49,582 --> 00:05:52,518
and that's why she turned the
wheel the wrong way.

69
00:05:52,518 --> 00:05:55,112
I'm so sorry.

70
00:05:55,755 --> 00:05:59,782
Don't try to escape by laughing,
you mokkori jerk!

71
00:06:03,496 --> 00:06:06,329
It happened just as I thought it would.

72
00:06:15,742 --> 00:06:20,372
Who were you keeping the brake
a secret from, Mr. Saeba?

73
00:06:21,013 --> 00:06:23,880
Wasn't it Ryo's fault?

74
00:06:24,384 --> 00:06:27,615
The expression on your face
caught my attention.

75
00:06:28,621 --> 00:06:30,723
If they thought it was an accident again,

76
00:06:30,723 --> 00:06:33,359
I would've been fired this time.

77
00:06:33,359 --> 00:06:36,028
The fact that you go to such lengths
to be a stuntwoman

78
00:06:36,028 --> 00:06:38,231
isn't just because you love it, is it?

79
00:06:38,231 --> 00:06:40,131
There must be some other reason.

80
00:06:41,634 --> 00:06:44,570
I started work as a stuntwoman
only a month ago,

81
00:06:44,570 --> 00:06:47,164
and I don't have any memories
before that time.

82
00:06:49,375 --> 00:06:51,244
When I'm performing a dangerous stunt,

83
00:06:51,244 --> 00:06:55,014
I feel as if I might get my lost memories
back for a moment.

84
00:06:55,014 --> 00:06:59,252
The more dangerous the stunt, the
stronger I feel like that, so...

85
00:06:59,252 --> 00:07:02,881
Stunts are the only clue you
have, aren't they?

86
00:07:03,456 --> 00:07:08,359
Yes, and that's why I can't quit now.

87
00:07:17,003 --> 00:07:19,301
Mr. Saeba, you're staying in this room also?

88
00:07:19,505 --> 00:07:24,177
Of course! I'm your bodyguard, aren't I?

89
00:07:24,177 --> 00:07:28,481
So, let's get in the same bed and sleep,
shall we, shall we, shall we?

90
00:07:28,481 --> 00:07:33,475
Yes, let's sleep! Ryo, there's a nice fluffy
bed ready for you on the roof.

91
00:07:38,157 --> 00:07:43,117
Damn! Kaori definitely underestimates me,
doesn't she?

92
00:07:48,868 --> 00:07:53,032
I wonder if Mr. Saeba is okay by himself
in a place like that?

93
00:07:54,807 --> 00:07:56,832
I'm sure he's fine.

94
00:07:58,344 --> 00:08:00,539
You're very gentle, Miss Yuki, aren't you?

95
00:08:01,714 --> 00:08:03,249
Since you're a stuntwoman,

96
00:08:03,249 --> 00:08:07,587
I thought you would be more masculine,
but you're very feminine,

97
00:08:07,587 --> 00:08:10,055
as if you were the daughter of
a noble family or something.

98
00:08:14,527 --> 00:08:17,096
Yes, Oikawa speaking.

99
00:08:17,096 --> 00:08:20,031
Who killed the robin?

100
00:08:29,275 --> 00:08:32,245
What's the matter? Is anything wrong?

101
00:08:32,245 --> 00:08:33,872
Wrong number.

102
00:08:34,780 --> 00:08:36,407
I see...

103
00:08:44,090 --> 00:08:47,582
One more time! Go!

104
00:08:59,038 --> 00:09:00,938
This time,

105
00:09:01,374 --> 00:09:02,966
I can do it!

106
00:09:04,176 --> 00:09:07,407
Who the hell opened the door so suddenly?!

107
00:09:08,381 --> 00:09:10,583
Wow, Yuki!

108
00:09:10,583 --> 00:09:13,953
I see, since I can't go to your room,

109
00:09:13,953 --> 00:09:16,114
you came all the way here to
see me, didn't you?

110
00:09:21,027 --> 00:09:24,497
No, why don't you come closer to me?

111
00:09:24,497 --> 00:09:26,198
Hey, hey, a little bit closer.

112
00:09:26,198 --> 00:09:28,868
What the hell is she thinking?!
Just a little more! Just thirty
centimeters more, Yuki!

113
00:09:28,868 --> 00:09:30,369
Why did she come to see Ryo?
Just a little more! Just thirty
centimeters more, Yuki!

114
00:09:30,369 --> 00:09:31,700
Why did she come to see Ryo?

115
00:09:32,939 --> 00:09:35,840
Why do I feel so bad about this?!

116
00:09:42,648 --> 00:09:43,616
Miss Yuki!

117
00:09:43,616 --> 00:09:44,844
Kaori, hurry!

118
00:09:47,520 --> 00:09:48,885
Look out!

119
00:10:04,236 --> 00:10:07,607
Did anything strange happen
while I was gone?

120
00:10:07,607 --> 00:10:10,910
Nothing much, just one phone call
and it was a wrong number.

121
00:10:10,910 --> 00:10:12,070
That's it!

122
00:10:12,745 --> 00:10:14,110
What do you mean?

123
00:10:15,314 --> 00:10:19,952
Actually, after the accident the other day,
I investigated that car,

124
00:10:19,952 --> 00:10:22,154
but there weren't any abnormalities
in the brakes or anywhere else.

125
00:10:22,154 --> 00:10:23,781
It was then that I understood.

126
00:10:24,890 --> 00:10:28,394
The series of accidents that
occurred during shooting

127
00:10:28,394 --> 00:10:33,354
were not caused by someone's tricks
but by her mind.

128
00:10:33,699 --> 00:10:35,428
By her mind?

129
00:10:35,835 --> 00:10:39,205
Unconscious hypnosis, in other words,
mind control.

130
00:10:39,205 --> 00:10:41,440
Mind control?

131
00:10:41,440 --> 00:10:43,509
Someone hypnotized her into
believing that the brakes

132
00:10:43,509 --> 00:10:45,773
would fail during filming, and she
would die in an accident.

133
00:10:46,412 --> 00:10:50,349
This time, someone used the phone
and hypnotized her

134
00:10:50,349 --> 00:10:52,485
to jump off the top of the building.

135
00:10:52,485 --> 00:10:56,922
Oh, no, trying to make her kill herself...

136
00:10:56,922 --> 00:10:58,287
It can't be!

137
00:10:58,891 --> 00:11:00,984
He's enjoying this.

138
00:11:02,161 --> 00:11:04,697
There are various types of killers.

139
00:11:04,697 --> 00:11:08,567
Some use guns, some use knives
to cut the body into pieces.

140
00:11:08,567 --> 00:11:13,139
In this case, the killer has to make
the target commit suicide,

141
00:11:13,139 --> 00:11:15,972
but it has to happen in public.

142
00:11:17,743 --> 00:11:19,870
Then tomorrow during the stunt...

143
00:11:22,314 --> 00:11:23,616
That's right.

144
00:11:23,616 --> 00:11:26,285
The stunt tomorrow will be on television.

145
00:11:26,285 --> 00:11:28,879
It will be the best opportunity for the killer.

146
00:11:29,955 --> 00:11:33,721
And at the same time, it will be
the end of his life.

147
00:11:43,869 --> 00:11:47,139
Wow, what a big gallery!

148
00:11:47,139 --> 00:11:52,244
Of course! It must be the first time
in Japanese movie history

149
00:11:52,244 --> 00:11:55,548
